{"title":"The Arresting Typography of the Sanborn Fire Insurance Maps","link":"https://kottke.org/24/12/the-arresting-typography-of-the-sanborn-fire-insurance-maps","date":1733776924000,"content":"\n        <p><img src=\"/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=1200,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/sanborn-map-covers-01.jpg\" srcset=\"/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=500,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/sanborn-map-covers-01.jpg 500w, /cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=1200,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/sanborn-map-covers-01.jpg 1200w\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1300\" height=\"1560\" alt=\"a very ornate cover for the Memphis fire insurance map\" /></p>\n\n<p>Several years ago, Brandon Silverman become obsessed with the lettering and typography on <a href=\"https://sanbornfiremaps.com/\">the fire insurance maps published by the Sanborn Map Company</a> in the late 19th and early 20th centuries.</p>\n\n<blockquote><p>Sanborn maps were designed to help insurance companies assess the fire risk of individual properties. They were highly detailed, showing the size, shape, and construction of buildings, as well as the materials used in their construction. This information was used by insurance companies to calculate the premium that a property owner would have to pay for fire insurance.</p></blockquote>\n\n<p>He even used the ornate, intricately designed covers as a model <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=jzxpFSbhTIY\">for his wedding invitation</a>. Silverman <a href=\"https://sanbornfiremaps.com/\">recently launched a site dedicated to the design of these fire maps</a>, collecting high-res digital scans of the art found on almost every cover and index page, over 3500 images in all. <a href=\"https://sanborn-fire-maps.myshopify.com/collections/cover-pages\">The cover pages</a> are particularly beautiful. Oh, and you can order prints of all the images as well.</p>\n\n<p><img src=\"/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=1200,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/sanborn-map-covers-02.jpg\" srcset=\"/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=500,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/sanborn-map-covers-02.jpg 500w, /cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=1200,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/sanborn-map-covers-02.jpg 1200w\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1300\" height=\"1924\" alt=\"a very ornate cover for the Queens fire insurance map\" /></p>\n\n<p><img src=\"/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=1200,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/sanborn-map-covers-03.jpg\" srcset=\"/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=500,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/sanborn-map-covers-03.jpg 500w, /cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=1200,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/sanborn-map-covers-03.jpg 1200w\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1300\" height=\"1508\" alt=\"a very ornate cover for the Flint fire insurance map\" /></p>\n\n<p><img src=\"/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=1200,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/sanborn-map-covers-04.jpg\" srcset=\"/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=500,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/sanborn-map-covers-04.jpg 500w, /cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=1200,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/sanborn-map-covers-04.jpg 1200w\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1300\" height=\"1872\" alt=\"a very ornate cover for the Brooklyn fire insurance map\" /></p>\n\n<p><img src=\"/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=1200,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/sanborn-map-covers-05.jpg\" srcset=\"/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=500,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/sanborn-map-covers-05.jpg 500w, /cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=1200,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/sanborn-map-covers-05.jpg 1200w\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1300\" height=\"1551\" alt=\"a very ornate cover for the Butte fire insurance map\" /></p>\n\n<p>Fun fact: Silverman first learned about the fire insurance maps from <a href=\"https://kottke.org/11/09/gorgeous-typography-on-fire-insurance-maps\">a 2011 post on kottke.org</a>.</p>\n\n        \n\n         <p><strong>Tags:</strong> <a href=\"https://kottke.org/tag/Brandon%20Silverman\">Brandon Silverman</a> Â· <a href=\"https://kottke.org/tag/design\">design</a> Â· <a href=\"https://kottke.org/tag/maps\">maps</a> Â· <a href=\"https://kottke.org/tag/typography\">typography</a></p>\n\n         <p>ðŸ’¬ <a href=\"https://kottke.org/24/12/the-arresting-typography-of-the-sanborn-fire-insurance-maps\">Join the discussion on kottke.org</a> â†’</p>\n\n    ","author":"Jason Kottke","siteTitle":"Kottke","siteHash":"89a883271b4598f9b33ebe87be70d38557bcd266e68aee521a8f93622e0ab723","entryHash":"a8e008d3f432155f8de0c24ef3f452b45d812dba84eb526a30d877c058064fe8","category":"Sites"}